gameRecap.title: Game Recap: Warriors 140, Bulls 131
gameRecap.excerpt: The Warriors defeated the Bulls, 140-131. Klay Thompson (30 points, six rebounds, six assists, seven 3PM) and Stephen Curry (27 points, nine assists, six 3PM) combined for 57 points for the Warriors, while Jonathan Kuminga added 24 points (4-4 3pt. FG) and five rebounds in the victory. DeMar DeRozan tallied 39 points, six rebounds and five assists for the Bulls in the losing effort. The Warriors improve to 18-20 on the season, while the Bulls snap a three-game winning streak as they fall to 18-22.
